# PX4 + NuttX boot script for Renode.
#
# The fixture (`Px4RenodeSitl::boot`) injects three variables before
# running this file via Renode's `-e` flag:
#
#   $slave  -- host-side pty path Renode attaches the console UART
#              to. The fixture opens the pty master end and drives
#              the shell (nsh / pxh) through it.
#   $bin    -- absolute path to the firmware ELF. Set from the
#              `PX4_RENODE_FIRMWARE` env var. May be a stock NuttX
#              nsh build (phase-13.1-lite) or a full PX4-on-NuttX
#              build (phase-13.1).
#   $repl   -- absolute path to the platform .repl. Avoids needing
#              `path add` plumbing on the Renode side.
#
# Both kinds of firmware use USART3 as the console on STM32H7
# (NuttX's `nucleo-h743zi` config picks USART3; PX4 boards on H7
# inherit that). The resc wires USART3 to the pty so the host
# fixture can drive the shell.
#
# Renode's monitor language uses `#` for comments. C-style `//`
# is a tokeniser error.

:name: PX4_RENODE_H743
:description: PX4 / NuttX firmware running on emulated STM32H743

mach create "PX4_RENODE_H743"
machine LoadPlatformDescription $repl

emulation CreateUartPtyTerminal "shellTerm" $slave true
connector Connect sysbus.usart3 shellTerm

macro reset
"""
    sysbus LoadELF $bin
"""
runMacro $reset

start
